FAIL_TO_PASS: when named pm and script arg and executableFile then spawn executableFile as command
when subcommand executable fails with other error and exitOverride then return in custom wrapper
when subcommand executable missing (ENOENT) then throw custom message
when execArgv --inspect=0 then spawn execArgs --inspect=0
when --inspect=1.2.3.4 then bump port
when --frozen-intrinsics then unchanged
when --inspect-unexpected then unchanged
when --inspect=1.2.3.4:100 then bump port
when script arg then search for local files
when execArgv empty then spawn execArgs empty
when named pm and no script arg or executableDir then spawn pm-sub as command
when --inspect=100 then bump port
when program sent SIGUSR1 then executableSubcommand sent signal too
when executableSubcommand succeeds then call exitOverride
when --inspect-brk then bump port
when --inspect-brk=1.2.3.4 then bump port
when name pm and script arg and relative executableFile then spawn local exec.js
when --inspect-port=100 then bump port
when subcommand executable not executable (EACCES) then throw custom message
when execArgv --inspect then spawn execArgs using port 9230
